@node DESCRIPTION "Description - What is it?"

  @{b}Description@{ub}
  @{b}-----------@{ub}

  CGXBlanker is a small ScreenBlanker for computers equipped with a
  CyberGraphics/Picasso96-supporting Gfx-Board.

  The blanker currently has the following Blanker-Modules:
  - Black  : just a black screen... ;)
  - Moire  : the classic colorful moire-blanker
  - Forest : colorful fractal trees
  - Spiral : an incredible rotating spiral
  - Flower : a very nice blanker which draws several elliptic objects
  - Pipe   : a interesting blanker which lets you fly trough a 3D pipe
  - Random : one of the blankers above is randomly chosen (except Black)

  CGXBlanker also supports the DPMS energy-saving methods of modern
  monitors. You can enable/disable this option and control the delay
  before the blanker switches to the DPMS mode(s).

  This blanker is a system-friendly commodity and you also have
  keyboard shortcuts for immediate blanking, immediate DPMS and quit.

  The blanker settings are easy to adjust with the CGXBlankerPrefs
  program - this is much simplier than changing Tooltypes by hand.

  Starting with V1.25, there is an ARexx port with allows the full
  control of CGXBlanker by external applications (for example: deactivate
  it before starting CDBurner-Software...)

@endnode

@node FEATURES "Features - Features of CGXBlanker"

  @{b}Features@{ub}
  @{b}--------@{ub}

  CGXBlanker...

   o supports (or better: needs) CyberGraphics or Picasso96
   o is small
   o has a prefs program with GUI
   o is fast (available for 020+ and 040+)
   o is a Commodity
   o has an ARexx interface
   o supports all three types of DPMS
   o is fully configurable
   o is systemfriendly designed
   o is freeware

@endnode

@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements - Hard-/Software-Requirements"

  @{b}Requirements@{ub}
  @{b}------------@{ub}

  @{b}o@{ub} AmigaOS 3.x+ (tested with OS 3.5 and OS3.1)
  @{b}o@{ub} GfxBoard running with CyberGraphX or Picasso96 and a
    Workbench/DefaultPublicScreen running in >=256 Colors
    (tested with CGXV3, 1152x900x16, OpusMagellanII)

  @{u}Testconfiguration@{uu}

  Amiga3000, OS3.5,
  CyberStorm 604e/200 & 68040/40, 144MB RAM
  CyberVision64, FrameMachine, AridadneII, HyperComZ3
  2.3GB and 4.5GB UW-SCSI-HD, Plextor UltraPlex32 CDROM,
  SyQuest270, Nomai750.c

@endnode

@node INSTALLATION "Installation - How to install"

  @{b}Installation@{ub}
  @{b}------------@{ub}


  Just double-click the "Install Software" icon and follow the
  installation steps displayed by the install-script.


  --- Only if you want to do it by hand, do the following ---

  1. According to your CPU-type, copy CGXBlanker0x0+ as
     "CGXBlanker" to your WBStartup

  2. Copy the CGXBlankerPrefs program to your SYS:Prefs directory

  3. Copy the "libs/wizard.library to libs:

  4. Thats it!

@endnode

@node CGXBLANKERPREFS "CGXBlankerPrefs"

  @{b}CGXBlankerPrefs@{ub}
  @{b}---------------@{ub}


  CGXBlankerPrefs lets you configure all features of CGXBlanker.

  @{fg shine}In the main section "General" you can select the global features:@{fg text}

  @{b}Blanker:@{ub}

       Blanktime: The time after the last mouse movement or keyboard input
                  until the blanker starts.

  Blanker Module: Here you can specify the blanker module you want to use.
                  Normally, here is "Random" selected, this means that every
                  time CGXBlanker blanks, it selects randomly a blanker.

  Ignore mousemovements while DPMS'ing:
                  -> If this checkbox is checked, CGXBlanker doesn't switch
                     on your monitor again, if you only move the mouse.
                     You will have to press a key on the keyboard to reactivate
                     it again.
                     Useful, if you always hated it that you monitor switched
                     on only because you hit the table where you have your
                     mouse... :)

  Don't blank if mouse is over the titlebar:
                 -> If checked, CGXBlanker doesn't blank if you have the mouse
                    pointer over the current screen titlebar.
                    This is useful, if you read long texts and don't want to get
                    disturbed by the blanker.



  @{b}Hotkeys:@{ub}

  Blankkey: This is the key combination which let's CGXBlanker immediately blank.

    Offkey: This is the shortcut for immediate doing DPMS (switching of the
            monitor).

   Quitkey: This hotkey asks CGXBlanker to quit (a requester will pop up).



  @{b}DPMS-Modes:@{ub}

  Each checkbox can enable or disable each DPMS (power saving) mode.
  The input in the right defines the number of seconds after blanking until the
  corresponding DPMS mode gets active (ony if enabled with the checkbox).



  @{fg shine}In the main section "Blankers" you can change the features of each blanker module.@{fg text}

  The checkbox "Enabled in Random-Mode" controls, if the current blanker module
  shall be available in Random-mode.

  The button "Test Blanker" lets CGXBlanker immediately show up the selected module
  with the current settings.

@endnode

@node AREXXPORT "ARexxPort - The ARexx interface"

  @{b}ARexxPort@{ub}
  @{b}---------@{ub}

  The ARexx port allows external programs to control CGXBlanker.
  Currently there are the followng commands:

  @{b}IMMEDIATE BLANK@{ub}
  Lets CGXBlanker immediate start blanking (just like pressing the Blankkey Hotkey).

  @{b}IMMEDIATE DPMS@{ub}
  Lets CGXBlanker immediate start DPMS (just like pressing the Offkey Hotkey).

  @{b}DEACTIVATE@{ub}
  This command deactivates the whole commodity CGXBlanker, you can reactivate it
  with Exchange or with "ACTIVATE".

  @{b}ACTIVATE@{ub}
  This command activates CGXBlanker after deactivating it with "DEACTIVATE" or Exchange.

  @{b}QUIT@{ub}
  This command quits CGXBlanker immediately.

  @{b}TEST <blanker module>@{ub}
  This command shows up the  given blanker module.
  Where <blanker module> is one of the following:
  BLACK, MOIRE, FOREST, FLOWER, SPIRAL, PIPE

@endnode

@node BUGSLIMITS "Bugs, Limitations - known problems"

  @{b}Bugs, limitations or known problems@{ub}
  @{b}-----------------------------------@{ub}

  - Some gfx-boards seems not to be able to do DPMS-functions.
    I can't change anything on this problem!

  If you have found a bug, please contact @{" me " link AUTHOR}.

@endnode

@node HISTORY "History - Program history"

  @{b}History@{ub}
  @{b}-------@{ub}

  V1.00: (27.03.1999)
         ** first public release **

  V1.10: (05.04.1999)
         - Added a Prefs-program with GUI for a simple configuration of
           the large number of blanker parameters. The Prefs-program
           now made the Tooltypes useless.
           There where also a lot of changes to the blankers:
         - Moire:
           o Selectable amount of lines
           o Full controlable random/fixed sped-settings
         - Forest:
           o Selectable number of trees to draw until clear-screen
           o Changeable colorstep which controls the colors used
             for every tree.
         - Spiral:
           o The spiral of the Spiral-Blanker now can rotate in both directions
             (controlable: random, clock wise, counter clock wise)
           o Selectable startangle (random or zero)
           o Three point styles: pixel, lines and blocks
           o Adjustable amoutn of points/elements
           o Controlable speed of the gradient
         - Added support for all three types of DMPS energy saving methods.
           (the old version only supported the OFF-mode)
           Thanks to Paul "ExiE" Strejcek for this suggestion!
         - Now you can control what blankers the random module can choose.

  V1.20: (15.11.1999)
         ** second public release **
         - Added a nice new blanker module "Flower". Many thanks to
           Roland Menzel for providing the very nice idea!!

  V1.21: (16.11.1999)
         - Made a mistake in the V1.20 release: I only included a 040
           optimized version. This will surely crash on machines with
           older CPUs... sorry... now there are two versions:
           One for 68020 and above and one for 68040 and above.
         - Added a installer script for easier installation...

  V1.22: (17.11.1999)
         - Removed a small bug in the installer script in expert mode.
           Thanks to Rico Schreckenbach for reporting the problem!

  V1.25: (03.03.2000)
         ** third public release **
         - CGXBlanker now blanks immediately again if another screen or
           window was brought to front by another application.
           Thanks to Ingo Musquinier for reporting this problem!
         - Added the ARexx-Interface to allow the control of CGXBlanker
           from external applications.
           Thanks, Andrew Bruno, for your initial idea (env-variable)!
         - Removed a problem with time-measurement. Now everything should
           be accurate!
           Thanks to Bill Ceaser for reporting this problem!
         - Added the "Don't blank if mouse is over titlebar" option.
           Thanks to Andrew Bruno for this idea!
         - Removed a compatibility problem (color-selection) with P96.
           Thanks to Rico Schreckenbach for reporting this!
         - The CGXBlankerPrefs program now informs the CGXBlanker
           immediately, if there is a new setting to use. You now
           also can immediately test the settings for each blanker by
           clicking "Test Blanker".
         - Added the Blanker "Pipe".
         - Added an AmigaGuide documentation.

@endnode

